Ask HN: Anyone up to help profile and improve latency of a Java database system?
text:
Over the course of the last at least half a year I've improved the latency of my evolutionary append-only DBS project[1] maintained in my spare time.

That said I'd like others to take a look as well[2].

Maybe anyone with more experience would like to have a look, too and help to improve latency further.

That's something I'm missing the most with my OSS over the last 10 years. Having discussions with others about ideas, concepts and some more help (despite one or two years in the past maybe).

Kind regards

Johannes

[1] https://github.com/sirixdb/sirix

[2] https://github.com/sirixdb/sirix/issues/558

Show HN: Schtate – Functional Data Containers with a Familiar API
text:
Looking for feedback on my library.

I work mainly with React at work, as data is passed down as props, we end up performing a lot of transformations and checks on it.

Most React developers leverage arrays heavily because the intuitive immutable, chainable API that JS arrays offer works really well with React's functional model. The purpose of this library is to make other types of data just as easy to work with by mirroring the Array API whenever possible, keeping immutability and chaining as first class features. It is not just for React developers, but anybody who has to manipulate data and hates having to write `if` statements.

The library has zero runtime dependencies and 100% test coverage.
